<br>
Yeah, being locked into the starting group is a bit troublesome, but most of the normal difficulty adventures are still beatable if you lose 1-2 people.  One of my wizards fell asleep in one and we still had no problem finishing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In LDoN, however, you are stuck where you are until you finish the mission lest you lose those oh so precious points.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You're only really stuck if you want to be.  If there's an important reason to leave, you only lose the points you were working towards at that time and maybe a little standing on a meaningless leaderboard.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know you all think it is great that you are moving about instead of pulling to a wall, but each adventure camp seems to have 2 or 3 cookie cutter zones that are identical in feel and very similar in appearance with no real variation except where the dead ends are<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's different at least, that's something in it's own right.  I've actually been pretty impressed with the zone design.  I've only done 10 or so adventures (most in Mistmoore) so maybe it'll change, but I haven't got much feeling of repetition in the zone design yet.  The zones may not be completely unique in look and feel, but with 1-2 exceptions, every other zone pre-LDoN has been completely identical everytime I've gone there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>you kill a bunch of weak ass trash mobs as fast as you can and once in a while kill some equally weak ass name who drops the same few craptastic loots every time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Normal difficulty is pretty tame for an elemental/time equiped group, but there's no reason you can't try hard if you're looking for a challenge. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How goddamm saturated with those stupid arrow summoning bags is the bazaar going to be in a month? Loot that anyone can get five times a day is not special no matter how nice it is.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As for loot saturating the Bazaar, how is that really any different than any other expansion?  The only real difference is instead of one person finding a valuable camp and monopolizing it, the loot is random.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And WTF ever happened to CR's?? In a real dungeon crawl you stand a reasonable chance of wiping and being faced with getting your corpses from behind crowds of respawned mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There was a point where I kept CR gear in the bank, but that ended 2 years ago when I got summon corpse.  With PoP, CRs were pretty much completely outdated, unless you were trying to beat some timed event.  I think people who enjoy CRs are in the minority.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
Overall, I like LDoN.  It's a decent distraction and it makes the exp grind a bit less painful.  Sure, the exp isn't as good as elementals, but instead of watching my exp bar, I'm having fun and surprised when I hear the ding.  The pricing system is a bit skewed, I think, since I'm looking at ~45 hours to buy just one piece of armor that's only an upgrade for me, because I haven't managed to get an elemental item for that slot.  The raids are insanely difficult, even on normal and the augments available for my armor are mediocre at best.<br>
<br>
At the worst, it should at least resolve some of the overcrowding. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5948">Duke Krazaak Crushbone</a> &lt<a href="http://www.hneguild.com">Heaven and Earth</a>&gt<BR>
